        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2018-10-22 14:25:12.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nI think sending the LSOM size is useful for implementing \"lfs find\" to be more efficient, but I think the \"lsom\" parameter to enable this for the whole filesystem should be removed. \n\nPlease return the size/lsize to userspace for lfs find, and this can be used for making decisions when the file size is requested with some large margin (eg. 1MB or more).  Please also include a test.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
