      },
      "date": "2019-06-11 04:59:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> I'm working on an updated version of this patch that includes an\n > llapi_get_lov_user_info() interface to fetch this data.\n\nOops, wrong patch.  I'm working on a new version of \"LU-11367 som: integrate LSOM with lfs find\".",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "23a383598c7aed5bb3f95c89fccb0af09f6ad47d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-15 14:30:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nNow that the statx() patch has landed, I don't think we would want to keep this patch?  Should it be abandoned?  I don't think LSOM would be usable for the whole filesystem unless it is read-only, since having the wrong LSOM size could lead to data corruption when accessing the file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "afbe5c9498204786d6a899a92e4bbcdd4cfe88fe",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 622,
        "name": "Qian Yingjin",
        "email": "qian@ddn.com",
        "username": "qian"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-15 14:33:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAgree to abandon.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
